# gen114: multi-step word problems. With three or more numbers, the solver folds
# an additive/subtractive chain left to right, clause by clause: the first number
# is the base, each later clause adds (default) or subtracts (if it carries a
# removal verb). Clauses split on then/and/poi/e and on commas. Held-out numbers
# and verbs; two-number problems still take the single-operation path.

# Add then subtract: 3 + 5 - 2 = 6.
> Tom has 3 apples, buys 5 more, then eats 2. How many apples does he have?
< 6.
# Subtract then add, held-out verbs (lost/found): 10 - 3 + 4 = 11.
> Anna had 10 marbles, lost 3, then found 4. How many does she have?
< 11.
# Three additions: 2 + 3 + 4 = 9.
> A box has 2 red, 3 blue and 4 green pens. How many pens in all?
< 9.